        "- Neutral is 4.6x more frequent than Negative\n",
        "- Will use class_weight during training + F1-macro as metric\n",
        "\n",
        "### Key Word Analysis Finding\n",
        "Common across all classes: eur, profit, net, sales, million\n",
        "â These are NOT discriminative â model must learn context\n",
        "\n",
        "Real discriminators:\n",
        "- Positive signal words: rose, increased, up, growth\n",
        "- Negative signal words: down, decreased, loss, fell\n",
        "- Neutral: company, shares, business, services (entity words)\n",
        "\n",
        "### Implication for Bi-LSTM\n",
        "Simple bag-of-words (TF-IDF) will fail here because:\n",
        "\"profit rose\" = positive\n",
        "\"profit fell\" = negative  \n",
        "Same word \"profit\" â opposite sentiment\n",
        "â Sequential models (Bi-LSTM) capture word ORDER\n",
        "â Transformers (DistilBERT) capture word CONTEXT\n",
        "â This is why deep learning beats classical ML here\n",
        "\n",
